===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|耳|t1=ear|又|t2=hand|ls=ic}} - to take the ear of fallen prey, a rite of hunters mentioned in the Rites of Zhou.

{{zh-x|大 獸 公 之，小 禽 私 之，獲 者 取 左 耳。|collapsed=y|ref=Zhouli}}

''{{w|Shuowen}}'' interprets it as taking the ear of an enemy instead. <!--(《又部》取：捕取也。从又从耳。《周禮》：「獲者取左耳。」《司馬法》曰：「載獻聝。」聝者，耳也。).--> However, Wang (2022) points out that there is no evidence that this actually happened in war.<ref>[https://www.fdgwz.org.cn/Web/Show/10934 王鵬遠 說“聝”]</ref>

